\Pr(Y=1|X=1)
\Pr(Y=2|X=1)
\Pr (X=1)=\frac{1}{10}+\frac{3}{10}=\frac{4}{10}
\Pr(Y=2|X=1)=\dfrac{3}{4}
\Pr(Y=1|X=1)=\frac{\Pr(X=1 \cap Y=1)}{\Pr(X=1)}=\frac{1/10}{4/10}=\frac{1}{4}.
